clang package.

LLVM version: @LLVM_VERSION@
Host triple: @TARGET_TRIPLE@

This prefix contains clang, lld, lldb, clang-tools-extra, the matching LLVM
SDK, and libc++/compiler-rt runtime files.

LLDB Python scripting is disabled in this package. Enabling it also requires
SWIG 4+ in the build dependency chain.

Target driver configuration files are installed next to clang in bin/.
Linux target cfg files expect sysroots outside this prefix:

  <clang-prefix>/../sysroot/<triple>

In Linux-host packages, the Windows GNU cfg files expect the host-arch
MinGW prefix outside this clang prefix:

  <clang-prefix>/../x86_64-w64-windows-gnu

In the x86_64-w64-windows-gnu native package, this prefix itself is the
Windows GNU sysroot. Its bin/, include/, and lib/ layout follows the
stage_mingw64 native package so bin/clang++.exe can run directly after
extraction.
